This paper proposes a novel framework for autoencoders and investigates the effect of the latent space transformation on learning generative models and denoising corrupted data. The paper focuses on machine learning and computer vision applications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of latent variables, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence research, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed framework using experimental results, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) sub-categories.
